308	   * ```typescript
309	   * const emailGatewayAdapter: ChannelGatewayAdapter<EmailAccount> = {
310	   *   startAccount: async (ctx) => {
311	   *     // Check availability (for backward compatibility)
312	   *     if (!ctx.channelRuntime) {
313	   *       ctx.log?.warn?.("channelRuntime not available - skipping AI features");
314	   *       return;
315	   *     }
316	   *
317	   *     // Use AI dispatch
318	   *     await ctx.channelRuntime.reply.dispatchReplyWithBufferedBlockDispatcher({
319	   *       ctx: { ... },
320	   *       cfg: ctx.cfg,
321	   *       dispatcherOptions: {
322	   *         deliver: async (payload) => {
323	   *           // Send reply via email
324	   *         },
325	   *       },
326	   *     });
327	   *   },
328	   * };
329	   * ```
330	   *
331	   * ## Backward Compatibility
332	   *
333	   * - This field is **optional** - channels that don't need it can ignore it
334	   * - Built-in channels (slack, discord, etc.) typically don't use this field
335	   *   because they can directly import internal modules
336	   * - External plugins should check for undefined before using
337	   *
338	   * @since Plugin SDK 2026.2.19
