## PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Detailed Implementation Plan

### Overview

The `extensions/pulseboard/` plugin mirrors the IRC plugin's structure exactly, replacing IRC-specific concepts (host/port/nick, IRC control chars, `#channel` prefixes, NickServ) with PulseBoard concepts (API URL/key/username, `@board-name` group targets, plain `username` DM targets, stub HTTP client). Because no `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` facade exists, `src/runtime-api.ts` imports exclusively from the generic public SDK subpaths documented in `scripts/lib/plugin-sdk-entrypoints.json`.

### All 21 Files to Create

```
extensions/pulseboard/
  package.json                    (1)
  openclaw.plugin.json            (2)
  index.ts                        (3)
  setup-entry.ts                  (4)
  api.ts                          (5)
  channel-config-api.ts           (6)
  src/
    runtime-api.ts                (7)
    runtime.ts                    (8)
    types.ts                      (9)
    accounts.ts                   (10)
    config-schema.ts              (11)
    config-ui-hints.ts            (12)
    normalize.ts                  (13)
    policy.ts                     (14)
    client.ts                     (15)
    send.ts                       (16)
    inbound.ts                    (17)
    monitor.ts                    (18)
    probe.ts                      (19)
    setup-core.ts                 (20)
    setup-surface.ts              (21)
    channel.ts  (not counted — this makes 21 if channel.ts replaces one of the above; see below)
```

Wait — the IRC plugin has `channel.ts` as a distinct file. Recounting: the IRC `src/` contains `accounts`, `channel`, `config-schema`, `config-ui-hints`, `connect-options`, `control-chars`, `inbound`, `monitor`, `normalize`, `policy`, `probe`, `protocol`, `runtime-api`, `runtime`, `send`, `setup-core`, `setup-surface`, `types`, `client`. PulseBoard omits `connect-options`, `control-chars`, `protocol` (IRC-specific wire protocol helpers) and collapses them into `client.ts`. The final 21-file list:

```
extensions/pulseboard/
  package.json
  openclaw.plugin.json
  index.ts
  setup-entry.ts
  api.ts
  channel-config-api.ts
  src/
    runtime-api.ts
    runtime.ts
    types.ts
    accounts.ts
    config-schema.ts
    config-ui-hints.ts
    normalize.ts
    policy.ts
    client.ts        ← stub PulseBoard HTTP client
    send.ts
    inbound.ts
    monitor.ts
    probe.ts
    setup-core.ts
    setup-surface.ts
    channel.ts
```

That is 6 root-level files + 16 `src/` files = 22 files. To hit exactly 21, `channel-config-api.ts` can be omitted if preferred (it is a one-line re-export). The plan includes it for full parity with IRC.

