Key findings about unavailable symbols from generic paths:

- `chunkTextForOutbound`: Only in `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`. PulseBoard implements a simple inline chunker in `channel.ts` (a plain function splitting on 4000-char boundaries at whitespace).
- `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase`: Only in `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`. PulseBoard uses `openclaw/plugin-sdk/direct-dm`'s `dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime` for DMs and implements a simplified group dispatch using the available pieces from `channel-policy`, `channel-inbound`, and `direct-dm`.
- `resolveControlCommandGate`, `deliverFormattedTextWithAttachments`, `GROUP_POLICY_BLOCKED_LABEL`, `resolveAllowlistProviderRuntimeGroupPolicy`, `resolveDefaultGroupPolicy`, `warnMissingProviderGroupPolicyFallbackOnce`: All available via `openclaw/plugin-sdk/config-runtime`.
- `BaseProbeResult`: Available from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` via the `channel-contract` re-export path. Confirmed it is exported in the SDK.
- `OutboundReplyPayload`: Define locally as `type OutboundReplyPayload = { text: string; mediaUrl?: string }` to avoid needing `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`.
- `DmPolicy`, `GroupPolicy`: Both exported from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/setup` as per `src/plugin-sdk/setup.ts` line 4.
- `MarkdownConfig`, `DmConfig`, `BlockStreamingCoalesceConfig`, `GroupToolPolicyConfig`, `GroupToolPolicyBySenderConfig`: Available from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema` via the schemas (`z.infer<typeof MarkdownConfigSchema>` etc.) OR from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/config-runtime` which exports them from `../config/types.js`.

The correct `src/runtime-api.ts` for PulseBoard:

