---

## Known Adaptation Points

1. **`resolveMentionGating` signature**: The exact parameter shape should be verified against `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-inbound`. The plan assumes `{ text, requireMention, botName }`. Adjust if the actual API differs.

2. **`dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime` signature**: Verify against `openclaw/plugin-sdk/direct-dm`. The plan provides a plausible signature matching how Nostr uses it.

3. **`ChannelConfigUiHints` type**: If not exported from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-helpers`, the `config-ui-hints.ts` can use an anonymous object type or `Record<string, {label: string; description: string; sensitive?: boolean}>`.

4. **`createScopedDmSecurityResolver` signature**: Verify the exact parameters against `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-helpers`. The IRC pattern uses `channelKey`, `resolvePolicy`, `resolveAllowFrom`, `policyPathSuffix`, `normalizeEntry`.

