# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

OpenClaw is a multi-channel AI gateway (pnpm monorepo). Bundled channel plugins live as workspace packages under `extensions/<id>/`. The user wants to add a fictional "PulseBoard" platform as a first-class channel plugin, following the same extension structure as existing channel plugins (IRC, Nostr, Telegram).

PulseBoard is a fictional real-time bulletin board platform where:
- Users post messages to named "boards" (group chats)
- Users can also send direct messages to one another
- Both `direct` and `group` chat types are supported
- 4000-character text chunk limit

**Constraint**: Do NOT modify any existing files. Only create new files in `extensions/pulseboard/`.

**Primary template**: IRC plugin (`extensions/irc/`) — simpler than Telegram/Discord, cleanly supports both direct and group chat.

---

## PulseBoard-Specific Concepts

| Concept | IRC equivalent | PulseBoard format |
|---|---|---|
| Group target | `#channel` | `@board-name` (e.g., `@general`) |
| DM target | `nick` | `username` (e.g., `alice`) |
| Auth credential | nick + password | `apiUrl` + `apiKey` + `username` |
| Env vars | `IRC_HOST`, `IRC_NICK` | `PULSEBOARD_API_URL`, `PULSEBOARD_API_KEY`, `PULSEBOARD_USERNAME` |
| "Channel" is a group | IRC channel starts with `#` or `&` | PulseBoard board starts with `@` |

---

## Critical Files to Read (Reference)

- `extensions/irc/src/channel.ts` — main plugin via `createChatChannelPlugin`
- `extensions/irc/src/accounts.ts` — account resolution pattern
- `extensions/irc/src/config-schema.ts` — Zod schema + `buildChannelConfigSchema`
- `extensions/irc/src/types.ts` — TypeScript types
- `extensions/irc/src/runtime.ts` — `createPluginRuntimeStore`
- `extensions/irc/src/runtime-api.ts` — internal barrel (imports from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`)
- `extensions/irc/src/normalize.ts` — target normalization
- `extensions/irc/src/setup-core.ts` — `ChannelSetupAdapter`
- `extensions/irc/src/setup-surface.ts` — `ChannelSetupWizard`
- `extensions/irc/src/send.ts` — outbound messaging
- `extensions/irc/src/inbound.ts` — inbound handling
- `extensions/irc/src/monitor.ts` — gateway monitor
- `extensions/irc/src/probe.ts` — status probe
- `extensions/irc/src/policy.ts` — group policy helpers

---

## Files to Create (21 files)

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── package.json                   (1)
├── openclaw.plugin.json           (2)
├── index.ts                       (3)
├── setup-entry.ts                 (4)
├── api.ts                         (5)
├── channel-config-api.ts          (6)
└── src/
    ├── runtime-api.ts             (7)   internal barrel
    ├── runtime.ts                 (8)
    ├── types.ts                   (9)
    ├── accounts.ts                (10)
    ├── config-schema.ts           (11)
    ├── config-ui-hints.ts         (12)
    ├── normalize.ts               (13)
    ├── policy.ts                  (14)
    ├── send.ts                    (15)
    ├── inbound.ts                 (16)
    ├── monitor.ts                 (17)
    ├── probe.ts                   (18)
    ├── setup-core.ts              (19)
    ├── setup-surface.ts           (20)
    └── channel.ts                 (21)   main plugin definition
```

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — `extensions/pulseboard/package.json`

Follow IRC's `package.json` (no `private: true`, no `npmSpec`):

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.2",
  "description": "OpenClaw PulseBoard channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "devDependencies": {
    "openclaw": "workspace:*"
  },
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "install": { "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1" },
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (Boards + DMs)",
      "detailLabel": "PulseBoard",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "docsLabel": "pulseboard",
      "blurb": "real-time bulletin board platform with named boards and direct messages.",
      "aliases": ["pulse-board", "pulse"]
    }
  }
}
```

**Notes**: No external runtime deps (fictional platform). `devDependencies` has `openclaw: "workspace:*"` so the SDK types are available at build time.

---

### Step 2 — `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

**Important**: The `id` must match `package.json openclaw.channel.id`, the default workspace folder name, and the config section key `channels.pulseboard`. This is the invariant enforced by `test/plugin-npm-release.test.ts`.

---

### Step 3 — `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts`

```typescript
import type { ChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { defineChannelPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { pulseBoardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
import { setPulseBoardRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export { pulseBoardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
export { setPulseBoardRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export default defineChannelPluginEntry({
  id: "pulseboard",
  name: "PulseBoard",
  description: "PulseBoard channel plugin",
  plugin: pulseBoardPlugin as ChannelPlugin,
  setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime,
});
```

---

### Step 4 — `extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts`

```typescript
import { defineSetupPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { pulseBoardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";

export default defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin);
```

---

### Step 5 — `extensions/pulseboard/api.ts`

Public API for any core that needs bundled-plugin helpers:

```typescript
export * from "./src/accounts.js";
export * from "./src/setup-surface.js";
```

---

### Step 6 — `extensions/pulseboard/channel-config-api.ts`

```typescript
export { PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema } from "./src/config-schema.js";
```

---

### Step 7 — `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime-api.ts`

Internal barrel that re-exports from **public** plugin-sdk paths only (no `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` facade exists — import from generic public paths):

```typescript
// Private runtime barrel for the bundled PulseBoard extension.
// Keep this barrel thin and aligned with the local extension surface.

export type { ChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
export type { OpenClawConfig } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
export { getChatChannelMeta } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";

export { DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id";

export type { PluginRuntime } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
export type { RuntimeEnv } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime";

export { PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-status";

export {
  createComputedAccountStatusAdapter,
  createDefaultChannelRuntimeState,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers";

export {
  buildPassiveChannelStatusSummary,
  runStoppablePassiveMonitor,
  resolveLoggerBackedRuntime,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/extension-shared";

export { logInboundDrop } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-inbound";
export {
  dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime,
  resolveInboundDirectDmAccessWithRuntime,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/direct-dm";

export {
  readStoreAllowFromForDmPolicy,
  resolveEffectiveAllowFromLists,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-policy";
```

**Why this approach**: IRC's `src/runtime-api.ts` re-exports from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc` which is a dedicated facade. Since creating a new `src/plugin-sdk/pulseboard.ts` facade would modify an existing area of the codebase (which is not allowed), PulseBoard instead imports directly from the generic public SDK subpaths. All paths used are in `scripts/lib/plugin-sdk-entrypoints.json`.

---

### Step 8 — `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts`

```typescript
import { createPluginRuntimeStore } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
import type { PluginRuntime } from "./runtime-api.js";

const { setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime, getRuntime: getPulseBoardRuntime } =
  createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>("PulseBoard runtime not initialized");

export { getPulseBoardRuntime, setPulseBoardRuntime };

export function clearPulseBoardRuntime() {
  setPulseBoardRuntime(undefined as unknown as PluginRuntime);
}
```

---

### Step 9 — `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts`

Defines all PulseBoard-specific TypeScript types. Types that IRC imports from `./runtime-api.js` (from the IRC facade) are defined locally here via `z.infer` or imported from public SDK paths.

```typescript
import type { DmPolicy, GroupPolicy } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/setup";
import type { OpenClawConfig } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import type { z } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/zod";
import type { MarkdownConfigSchema, ToolPolicySchema } from "./config-schema.js";

// Board-level config (per-board overrides)
export type PulseBoardGroupConfig = {
  requireMention?: boolean;
  tools?: z.infer<typeof ToolPolicySchema>;
  enabled?: boolean;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  skills?: string[];
  systemPrompt?: string;
};

// Account-level config (merged from top-level + per-account)
export type PulseBoardAccountConfig = {
  name?: string;
  enabled?: boolean;
  apiUrl?: string;
  apiKey?: string;
  username?: string;
  dmPolicy?: DmPolicy;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  defaultTo?: string;
  groupPolicy?: GroupPolicy;
  groupAllowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  boards?: Record<string, PulseBoardGroupConfig>;
  markdown?: z.infer<typeof MarkdownConfigSchema>;
  textChunkLimit?: number;
};

// Top-level config (can have sub-accounts)
export type PulseBoardConfig = PulseBoardAccountConfig & {
  accounts?: Record<string, PulseBoardAccountConfig>;
  defaultAccount?: string;
};

// Augmented OpenClawConfig with pulseboard channel
export type CoreConfig = OpenClawConfig & {
  channels?: OpenClawConfig["channels"] & {
    pulseboard?: PulseBoardConfig;
  };
};

// Shape of an inbound message from PulseBoard
export type PulseBoardInboundMessage = {
  messageId: string;
  /** Conversation peer: board name (with @) for groups, sender username for DMs */
  target: string;
  rawTarget?: string;
  senderUsername: string;
  text: string;
  timestamp: number;
  isGroup: boolean;
};

// Status probe result
export type PulseBoardProbe = {
  ok: boolean;
  apiUrl: string;
  username: string;
  latencyMs?: number;
  error?: string;
};
```

**Note on type imports**: `DmPolicy` and `GroupPolicy` are available from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/setup`. `MarkdownConfigSchema` and `ToolPolicySchema` are imported from the local `./config-schema.js` — types are inferred from the Zod schemas. `PulseBoardProbe` is defined locally (no `BaseProbeResult` import needed since it's only available via channel-specific SDK facades).

---

### Step 10 — `extensions/pulseboard/src/accounts.ts`

Follow the IRC `accounts.ts` pattern exactly, replacing IRC concepts with PulseBoard:

```typescript
import { createAccountListHelpers } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers";
import { DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID, normalizeAccountId } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id";
import { resolveMergedAccountConfig } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution";
import { normalizeResolvedSecretInputString } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input";
import type { CoreConfig, PulseBoardAccountConfig } from "./types.js";

export type ResolvedPulseBoardAccount = {
  accountId: string;
  enabled: boolean;
  name?: string;
  configured: boolean;
  apiUrl: string;
  username: string;
  apiKey: string;
  apiKeySource: "env" | "config" | "none";
  config: PulseBoardAccountConfig;
};

const { listAccountIds: listPulseBoardAccountIds, resolveDefaultAccountId: resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId } =
  createAccountListHelpers("pulseboard", { normalizeAccountId });
export { listPulseBoardAccountIds, resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId };

function mergePulseBoardAccountConfig(cfg: CoreConfig, accountId: string): PulseBoardAccountConfig {
  return resolveMergedAccountConfig<PulseBoardAccountConfig>({
    channelConfig: cfg.channels?.pulseboard as PulseBoardAccountConfig | undefined,
    accounts: cfg.channels?.pulseboard?.accounts as Record<string, Partial<PulseBoardAccountConfig>> | undefined,
    accountId,
    omitKeys: ["defaultAccount"],
    normalizeAccountId,
  });
}

function resolveApiKey(accountId: string, merged: PulseBoardAccountConfig): { apiKey: string; source: "env" | "config" | "none" } {
  if (accountId === DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID) {
    const envKey = process.env.PULSEBOARD_API_KEY?.trim();
    if (envKey) return { apiKey: envKey, source: "env" };
  }
  const configKey = normalizeResolvedSecretInputString({
    value: merged.apiKey,
    path: `channels.pulseboard.accounts.${accountId}.apiKey`,
  });
  if (configKey) return { apiKey: configKey, source: "config" };
  return { apiKey: "", source: "none" };
}

export function resolvePulseBoardAccount(params: { cfg: CoreConfig; accountId?: string | null }): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount {
  const hasExplicitAccountId = Boolean(params.accountId?.trim());
  const baseEnabled = params.cfg.channels?.pulseboard?.enabled !== false;

  const resolve = (accountId: string): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount => {
    const merged = mergePulseBoardAccountConfig(params.cfg, accountId);
    const enabled = baseEnabled && merged.enabled !== false;

    const apiUrl = (merged.apiUrl?.trim() ||
      (accountId === DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID ? process.env.PULSEBOARD_API_URL?.trim() : "") || "").trim();
    const username = (merged.username?.trim() ||
      (accountId === DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID ? process.env.PULSEBOARD_USERNAME?.trim() : "") || "").trim();
    const { apiKey, source } = resolveApiKey(accountId, merged);

    return {
      accountId,
      enabled,
      name: merged.name?.trim() || undefined,
      configured: Boolean(apiUrl && username),
      apiUrl,
      username,
      apiKey,
      apiKeySource: source,
      config: { ...merged, apiUrl, username },
    };
  };

  const normalized = normalizeAccountId(params.accountId);
  const primary = resolve(normalized);
  if (hasExplicitAccountId || primary.configured) return primary;

  const fallbackId = resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId(params.cfg);
  if (fallbackId === primary.accountId) return primary;
  const fallback = resolve(fallbackId);
  return fallback.configured ? fallback : primary;
}

export function listEnabledPulseBoardAccounts(cfg: CoreConfig): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount[] {
  return listPulseBoardAccountIds(cfg)
    .map((accountId) => resolvePulseBoardAccount({ cfg, accountId }))
    .filter((account) => account.enabled);
}
