# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

OpenClaw is a multi-channel AI gateway (pnpm monorepo). Bundled channel plugins live as workspace packages under `extensions/<id>/`. The user wants to add a fictional "PulseBoard" platform as a first-class channel plugin, following the same extension structure as existing channel plugins (IRC, Nostr, Telegram).

PulseBoard is a fictional real-time bulletin board platform where:
- Users post messages to named "boards" (group chats)
- Users can also send direct messages to one another
- Both `direct` and `group` chat types are supported
- 4000-character text chunk limit

**Constraint**: Do NOT modify any existing files. Only create new files in `extensions/pulseboard/`.

**Primary template**: IRC plugin (`extensions/irc/`) — simpler than Telegram/Discord, cleanly supports both direct and group chat.

---

## PulseBoard-Specific Concepts

| Concept | IRC equivalent | PulseBoard format |
|---|---|---|
| Group target | `#channel` | `@board-name` (e.g., `@general`) |
| DM target | `nick` | `username` (e.g., `alice`) |
| Auth credential | nick + password | `apiUrl` + `apiKey` + `username` |
| Env vars | `IRC_HOST`, `IRC_NICK` | `PULSEBOARD_API_URL`, `PULSEBOARD_API_KEY`, `PULSEBOARD_USERNAME` |
| "Channel" is a group | IRC channel starts with `#` or `&` | PulseBoard board starts with `@` |

---

## Critical Files to Read (Reference)

- `extensions/irc/src/channel.ts` — main plugin via `createChatChannelPlugin`
- `extensions/irc/src/accounts.ts` — account resolution pattern
- `extensions/irc/src/config-schema.ts` — Zod schema + `buildChannelConfigSchema`
- `extensions/irc/src/types.ts` — TypeScript types
- `extensions/irc/src/runtime.ts` — `createPluginRuntimeStore`
- `extensions/irc/src/runtime-api.ts` — internal barrel (imports from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`)
- `extensions/irc/src/normalize.ts` — target normalization
- `extensions/irc/src/setup-core.ts` — `ChannelSetupAdapter`
- `extensions/irc/src/setup-surface.ts` — `ChannelSetupWizard`
- `extensions/irc/src/send.ts` — outbound messaging
- `extensions/irc/src/inbound.ts` — inbound handling
- `extensions/irc/src/monitor.ts` — gateway monitor
- `extensions/irc/src/probe.ts` — status probe
- `extensions/irc/src/policy.ts` — group policy helpers

---

## Files to Create (21 files)

